<DOC><DOCNO> AP890413-0154 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-13-89 2045EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-EscapeeHaircut     04-13 0208</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Escapee Haircut,0213</SECOND><HEAD>Escaped Prisoner Caught After Stop At Barber Shop</HEAD><DATELINE>BILLINGS, Mont. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A prisoner who escaped from a courthousestopped two blocks away to get a shave and a haircut and wascaptured afterward still wearing his handcuffs and a waist chain.   Cathy Brekke said the man came into her barbershop Tuesday andwas in a hurry to have his hair cut and his beard and moustacheshaved off.   ``He was sweating like a pig and wouldn't take off his jacket,''she said. ``He was real uncomfortable when he was getting his hairshampooed. He told me he'd been hit by a truck.''   Brekke said she didn't noticie anything unusual until heremained in the shop to use the telephone after his haircut.   She said she ``kept seeing something metal,'' though thehandcuffs were under his sleeves and the chain around his waist wasinside his sportscoat. She finally realized he was handcuffed andcalled police from a nearby restaurant.   Police arrested Rick Savaria, 33, who had escaped two hoursearlier from a line of eight prisoners at the county courthouse,said Undersheriff Chuck Maxwell.   Maxwell said authorities will seek felony escape charges againstSavaria, who had been awaiting sentencing on a theft charge.</TEXT></DOC>